rComments: He's something to get over at first, but in the end he's a great guy. Very helpful and intelligent. Makes a lot of cheesy jokes, but that just adds to the enjoyment.
SO HOT! says the words 'basically' far too often but honestly, when you're that good looking, does it really matter?

weird, I don't rate people either, however, the second I saw him, all I could think was "10! TEN!" Once you get over how ridiculously good looking he is, he's very intelligent, funny, makes the course interesting.  Do NOT be afraid to ask him for help, he's a cool guy and will do as much as he can for you.
I dont rate people on scales, but he's a 10, a perfect 10!!! Gorgeous!!!! anyway...interesting course dates are kind of boring, but he's a good prof.  Really funny too.

The course material is interesting and Pagliaroli teaches right from the book. While some lectures get bogged down in dry names and dates, Pagliaroli is always quick to throw in an anecdote or a comment about wine. He is fairly new to lecturing, but deals well with the material. Over all, a great guy, always funny, and eager to engage the class
